                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract1253-1">Gregory Pīrānguŝnasp was a Zoroastrian
          Convert from the family of Mihran. He was imprisoned by the Byzantines and treated well by
          Justin I. He converted to Christianity. He was freed by a truce with Kusro, but his family
          put him to death in 542.</note>
